rounds.event: Constance Markievicz, while detained in Holloway prison, becomes the first woman to be elected Member of Parliament (MP) to the British House of Commons.
deaths: Olavo Bilac, Brazilian poet and journalist

rounds.event: A magnitude 5.6 earthquake hits Newcastle, New South Wales, Australia, killing 13 people.
deaths: Hermann Oberth, Romanian-German physicist and engineer

rounds.event: Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501 crashes into the Karimata Strait en route from Surabaya to Singapore, killing all 162 people aboard.
American businesswoman Muriel Siebert becomes the first woman to own a seat on the New York Stock Exchange.
deaths: Katharine McCormick, American biologist and philanthropist

rounds.event: Chin Peng, David Marshall and Tunku Abdul Rahman meet in Baling, Malaya to try and resolve the Malayan Emergency situation.
